<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25563</anchor> <rss>anon.153.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Proof</taxon> <addr>anon.153</addr>  <route>anon.153.xml</route>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <link href="erct-002Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002Q" title="Sections of sections are unique">Sections of sections</link> and <link href="erct-002R.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002R" title="Retractions of retractions are unique">retractions of retractions</link> are unique.
</mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25564</anchor> <rss>erct-002S.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-002S</addr>  <route>erct-002S.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">Biinverses</link> are unique</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002S.agda" type="external">erct-002S.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>The type of <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinverses</link> of a given function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   
 
</mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25565</anchor> <rss>erct-002Q.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002Q</addr>  <route>erct-002Q.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Sections and retractions">Sections</link> of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Sections and retractions">sections</link> are unique</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002Q.agda" type="external">erct-002Q.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> be a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Sections and retractions">section</link> of some <tex>r \colon  B \to  A</tex>; the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Sections and retractions">sections</link> of <tex>f</tex> is, then, a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25566</anchor> <rss>anon.155.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Proof</taxon> <addr>anon.155</addr>  <route>anon.155.xml</route>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Using the <link href="erct-0015.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0015" title="The univalence principle for dependent functions">univalence principle for dependent function spaces</link>, we can see that the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Sections and retractions">sections</link> of <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f \circ  -</tex> at <tex>1_{ B }</tex>, using the <link href="erct-0023.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0023" title="The univalence principle for sections">univalence principle for sections</link>.</p>

 <p>To show that the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Sections and retractions">sections</link> of <tex>f</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">proposition</link>, we may assume beforehand that we have such a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Sections and retractions">section</link> of <tex>f</tex>; therefore, because we have assumed a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Sections and retractions">retraction</link> of <tex>f</tex> already, we know that <tex>f</tex> is <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> and <link href="erct-002N.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002N" title="Biinvertible maps are contractible">therefore</link> that <tex>f</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>. Because <link href="erct-0026.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0026" title="Propositions are closed under retracts">propositions are closed under retracts</link>, it suffices to show that the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f \circ  -</tex> at <tex>1_{ B }</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">proposition</link>, which <link href="erct-001K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001K" title="Contractible types are propositions">follows</link> because <tex>f</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25567</anchor> <rss>erct-002R.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002R</addr>  <route>erct-002R.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Sections and retractions">Retractions</link> of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Sections and retractions">retractions</link> are unique</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002R.agda" type="external">erct-002R.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> be a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Sections and retractions">retraction</link> of some <tex>s \colon  B \to  A</tex>; the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Sections and retractions">retractions</link> of <tex>f</tex> is, then, a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25568</anchor> <rss>anon.154.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Proof</taxon> <addr>anon.154</addr>  <route>anon.154.xml</route>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Analogous to the <link href="erct-002Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002Q" title="Sections of sections are unique">corresponding result for sections of sections</link>, using the fact that the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Sections and retractions">retractions</link> of <tex>f</tex> can be seen to be a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>- \circ  f</tex> at <tex>1_{ A }</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks/> <references/></backmatter></tree>